Description: Harry, suffering like this proves you are still a man! This pain is part of being human...the fact that you can feel pain like this is your greatest strength.

Short Description: And so he spoke, and so he spoke, that Lord of Castamere, but now the rains weep o'er his hall, with no one there to hear. Yes, now the rains weep o'er his hall, and not a soul to hear.

Description: We’ve all got both light and dark inside us. What matters is the part we choose to act on. That’s who we really are.
To the well-organized mind, death is but the next great adventure.
Short Description: ... a mind needs books as a sword needs a whetstone, if it is to keep its edge.

Description: Happiness can be found even in the darkest of times if only one remembers to turn on the light.
Dark and difficult times lie ahead. Soon we must all face the choice between what is right and what is easy.
There are some things you can't share without ending up liking each other, and knocking out a twelve-foot mountain troll is one of them.
Short Description: Never forget who you are. The rest of the world won't. Wear it like an armor and it can never be used against you.

Description: It is the unknown we fear when we look upon death and darkness, nothing more.
It does not do to dwell on dreams and forget to live.
Short Description: And I have a tender spot in my heart for cripples and bastards and broken things.

Description: Never trust anything that can think for itself if you can't see where it keeps its brain.
Short Description: Some old wounds never truly heal, and bleed again at the slightest word.

Description: If you want to know what a man’s like, take a good look at how he treats his inferiors, not his equals.
Short Description: A lion doesn't concern itself with the opinion of sheep.

Description: Words are in my not-so-humble opinion, the most inexhaustible form of magic we have, capable both of inflicting injury and remedying it.
Short Description: Once you’ve accepted your flaws, no one can use them against you.
